highlights.description: Growing up in a very conservative town, "You just knew what you could say and how to say it"
Story about man screaming "Why can't you speak English" to loud speaker in Woodman's, an hour before their LVN conversation
"I have recently bumped into... 'I'm mad and I'm not gonna take it anymore direction'" like in interactions with school board candidates and at the meeting about the Park Street grocery store"

It has been easier for me to connect to women and people of color telling their stories when I have reflected on my own history of being bullied and having to deal with the way boys are expected to be OK with casual violence
Jury can't handle being called prejudice
